      • updateAlerts

        @PUT
 @Path(value="/{username}/alerts")
 @Produces(value="application/vnd.ilandcloud.api.v0.5+json")
 @Consumes(value="application/vnd.ilandcloud.api.v0.5+json")
AlertUpdateReport updateAlerts(@PathParam(value="username")
                                                                                                                                                                                                 String username,
                                                                                                                                                                                                 List<Alert> alerts,
                                                                                                                                                                                                 @QueryParam(value="orgUuid")
                                                                                                                                                                                                 Set<String> entityUuids,
                                                                                                                                                                                                 @QueryParam(value="type")
                                                                                                                                                                                                 Set<AlertType> types)
        Update a list of alerts. Returns a list of alerts that were successfully updated as well as list of failed to update alerts. This endpoint will only update the alerts for the user / organization combos in which the given list of alerts touches. E.g. if the user has 3 orgs and the alerts given in the body only correspond to 2 of those 3 orgs, then any existing alerts corresponding to the 3rd org will be untouched during this update. This endpoint will also create missing alerts if the alert uuid is passed in as null. Entity UUIDs can be provided to filter alerts updates scope by by entity. Alert types can be provided to filter alerts updates scope by alert type. The list of alert types available from this endpoint are:
        • vulnerability
        • antimalware
        • intrusion_protection
        • web_reputation
        • firewall
        • integrity
        • log_inspection
        Returns:
        list of alerts that were updated as well as ones that could not be updated

      • createAlert

        @POST
 @Path(value="/{username}/alerts")
 @Produces(value="application/vnd.ilandcloud.api.v0.5+json")
 @Consumes(value="application/vnd.ilandcloud.api.v0.5+json")
Alert createAlert(@PathParam(value="username")
                                                                                                                                                                                     String username,
                                                                                                                                                                                     Alert alert)
        Create a new alert. The list of alert types available from this endpoint are:
        • vulnerability
        • antimalware
        • intrusion_protection
        • web_reputation
        • firewall
        • integrity
        • log_inspection
        A synopsis of the additional fields (besides the ones documented in the model schema) availble to particular types of alrerts at creation time are:
        vulnerability
        • org_uuid: (required) organization uuid
        • equality: (required)equality relation (">=" or "=")
        • severity_threshold: (required) severity threshold ("low", "info", "medium", "high" or "critical")
        • host_addresses: (optional) a set of host addresses to apply the alert too (ip addreses) e.g. {"192.168.0.1", "192.168.0.2"}
        antimalware
        • org_uuid: (required) organization uuid
        intrusion_protection
        • org_uuid: (required) organization uuid
        web_reputation
        • org_uuid: (required) organization uuid
        firewall
        • org_uuid: (required) organization uuid
        integrity
        • org_uuid: (required) organization uuid
        • equality: (required) equality relation (">=" or "=")
        • severity_threshold: (required) severity threshold ("low", "info", "medium", "high" or "critical")
        log_inspection
        • org_uuid: (required) organization uuid
        • equality: (required) equality relation (">=" or "=")
        • severity_threshold: (required) severity threshold ("low", "info", "medium", "high" or "critical")
        Returns:
        the new alert
